{
  "info": {
    "name": "SignatureBack Integration API",
    "description": "Integration endpoints for CpaDesk ↔ SignatureBack platform.\n\nFlow:\n1. CpaDesk generates a signed JWT (HMAC-HS256) with the shared secret.\n2. User's browser is redirected to: https://chatapp.sbs/lof?token=<JWT>\n3. SignatureBack validates the token, logs in the user, and redirects to the correct page.\n4. After signing is complete, SignatureBack calls back CpaDesk's endpoints.\n\nSHARED SECRET: Provided separately over a secure channel.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "https://chatapp.sbs",
      "description": "SignatureBack production URL"
    },
    {
      "key": "shared_secret",
      "value": "ZXNpZ24ubXljcGFkZXNrLmNvbUAyMDI2",
      "description": "HMAC-HS256 shared secret — replace with the production secret"
    },
    {
      "key": "launch_token",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-generated by pre-request script"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "ESign Flow",
      "description": "New flow — uses ESignRequestID from ESignRequests table. Role is read from DB (no role in JWT).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Launch — Admin (CPAAdmin assigns regions)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// ── Generate HMAC-HS256 JWT ──────────────────────────────────────────",
                  "function base64url(str) {",
                  "    return btoa(str).replace(/=/g,'').replace(/\\+/g,'-').replace(/\\//g,'_');",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "const header  = base64url(JSON.stringify({ alg: 'HS256', typ: 'JWT' }));",
                  "const payload = base64url(JSON.stringify({",
                  "    eSignRequestId: parseInt(pm.variables.get('esign_request_id')),",
                  "    token:          pm.variables.get('login_token'),",
                  "    jti:            pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}'),",
                  "    exp:            Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + 300  // 5 min expiry",
                  "}));",
                  "",
                  "const signingInput = header + '.' + payload;",
                  "const secret       = pm.variables.get('shared_secret');",
                  "const hash         = CryptoJS.HmacSHA256(signingInput, secret);",
                  "const sig          = hash.toString(CryptoJS.enc.Base64)",
                  "                         .replace(/=/g,'').replace(/\\+/g,'-').replace(/\\//g,'_');",
                  "",
                  "pm.variables.set('launch_token', signingInput + '.' + sig);",
                  "console.log('Generated token for ESignRequestID:', pm.variables.get('esign_request_id'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has access_token', () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property('access_token'));",
                  "pm.test('Has next_route',   () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property('next_route'));",
                  "pm.test('Role is ADMIN',    () => pm.expect(json.role).to.eql('ADMIN'));",
                  "console.log('Next route:', json.next_route);",
                  "if (json.access_token) { pm.environment.set('admin_jwt', json.access_token); }"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/integration/launch?token={{launch_token}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "integration", "launch"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"{{launch_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "ESign flow — Admin launch.\n\nESignRequests row must have AssignedRole = 'CPAAdmin'.\nReturns next_route = /admin/documents/{id}/regions\n\nSet collection variable 'esign_request_id' to the target ESignRequestID.\nSet 'login_token' to the LoginDetail.Token of the admin (or leave empty to skip verification)."
          },
          "variable": [
            { "key": "esign_request_id", "value": "1", "description": "ESignRequestID from ESignRequests table" },
            { "key": "login_token",      "value": "",  "description": "LoginDetail.Token of the admin user (optional)" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Launch — Client/Signer (signs the document)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function base64url(str) {",
                  "    return btoa(str).replace(/=/g,'').replace(/\\+/g,'-').replace(/\\//g,'_');",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "const header  = base64url(JSON.stringify({ alg: 'HS256', typ: 'JWT' }));",
                  "const payload = base64url(JSON.stringify({",
                  "    eSignRequestId: parseInt(pm.variables.get('esign_request_id')),",
                  "    token:          pm.variables.get('login_token'),",
                  "    jti:            pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}'),",
                  "    exp:            Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + 300",
                  "}));",
                  "",
                  "const signingInput = header + '.' + payload;",
                  "const secret       = pm.variables.get('shared_secret');",
                  "const hash         = CryptoJS.HmacSHA256(signingInput, secret);",
                  "const sig          = hash.toString(CryptoJS.enc.Base64)",
                  "                         .replace(/=/g,'').replace(/\\+/g,'-').replace(/\\//g,'_');",
                  "",
                  "pm.variables.set('launch_token', signingInput + '.' + sig);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has access_token', () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property('access_token'));",
                  "pm.test('Role is SIGNER',   () => pm.expect(json.role).to.eql('SIGNER'));",
                  "console.log('Next route:', json.next_route);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/integration/launch?token={{launch_token}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "integration", "launch"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"{{launch_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "ESign flow — Client/Signer launch.\n\nESignRequests row must have AssignedRole = 'Client'.\nReturns next_route = /signer/documents/{id}/sign\n\nSAME ESignRequestID as admin — CpaDesk updates AssignedRole from 'CPAAdmin' to 'Client' after admin prepares the document."
          },
          "variable": [
            { "key": "esign_request_id", "value": "1",  "description": "Same ESignRequestID used by admin" },
            { "key": "login_token",      "value": "",   "description": "LoginDetail.Token of the client (optional)" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Health Check",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Server is up', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Status ok',    () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('ok'));"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["health"]
        },
        "description": "Verify the SignatureBack server is running."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "📘 Reference — JWT Payload Structure",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/integration/launch?token={{launch_token}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "integration", "launch"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"<HMAC-HS256 signed JWT — see description>\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "## JWT Claims Reference\n\n### ESign Flow (recommended)\n```json\n{\n  \"eSignRequestId\": 1,\n  \"token\": \"<LoginDetail.Token of the launching user — optional>\",\n  \"jti\": \"<unique UUID — must be different every time>\",\n  \"exp\": <unix timestamp, 5 minutes from now>\n}\n```\n\n### Rules\n- Algorithm: **HS256** (HMAC-SHA256)\n- `jti` must be a fresh UUID on every button click — reusing causes 401\n- `exp` must also be fresh (5 min window recommended)\n- Role is NOT in the JWT — it is read from `ESignRequests.AssignedRole` in the database\n\n### AssignedRole values\n| AssignedRole | Who sees it | Redirected to |\n|---|---|---|\n| `CPAAdmin` or `CPAUser` | Admin (assigns regions) | `/admin/documents/{id}/regions` |\n| `Client` | Signer (signs document) | `/signer/documents/{id}/sign` |\n\n### Callbacks we send to CpaDesk\nAfter admin saves regions:\n- `POST {cpaDesk_base_url}/api/ESign/ProcessESignDocumentPrepared`\n  ```json\n  { \"ESignRequestID\": 1, \"FileBytes\": \"<base64 PDF>\" }\n  ```\n\nAfter signer submits:\n- `POST {cpaDesk_base_url}/api/ESign/ProcessESignDocumentPrepared`\n  ```json\n  { \"ESignRequestID\": 1, \"FileBytes\": \"<base64 signed PDF>\" }\n  ```\n- `POST {cpaDesk_base_url}/api/ESign/ProcessESignCompletion`\n  ```json\n  { \"ESignRequestID\": 1 }\n  ```\n\n> Base URL is extracted automatically from the decrypted `FileURL` field in `ESignRequests` — no hardcoding needed."
      }
    }
  ]
}
